1
00:00:00,333 --> 00:00:01,800
now you're really cooking

2
00:00:02,433 --> 00:00:03,700
you've got more than gusto

3
00:00:03,900 --> 00:00:05,233
you've got goals

4
00:00:05,466 --> 00:00:06,600
a power system

5
00:00:06,733 --> 00:00:08,133
magical remedies

6
00:00:08,200 --> 00:00:09,800
and a smooth ride through MV

7
00:00:10,533 --> 00:00:12,700
but the quest book has you spooked

8
00:00:13,133 --> 00:00:14,866
things are getting more complicated quickly

9
00:00:15,466 --> 00:00:16,400
chemical lines

10
00:00:16,400 --> 00:00:17,866
multi step automation

11
00:00:17,866 --> 00:00:19,233
new mods and metals

12
00:00:19,333 --> 00:00:21,500
and brand new circuit components you've never seen

13
00:00:22,000 --> 00:00:22,933
what in the world

14
00:00:23,700 --> 00:00:24,533
gregtech

15
00:00:24,533 --> 00:00:25,333
that's what

16
00:00:25,733 --> 00:00:29,066
welcome back to the beginners guide to GregTech New Horizons

17
00:00:29,066 --> 00:00:30,400
today we upgrade

18
00:00:30,733 --> 00:00:32,400
if you're waiting to take things to the next level

19
00:00:32,400 --> 00:00:33,666
you're in the right place

20
00:00:33,666 --> 00:00:34,700
this is episode 7

21
00:00:35,300 --> 00:00:36,100
MV

22
00:00:52,800 --> 00:00:54,333
there's not a ton of preamble this time

23
00:00:54,800 --> 00:00:56,266
you should have a goal for your power system

24
00:00:56,266 --> 00:00:58,200
and maybe some goodies you already know you want to grab

25
00:00:58,333 --> 00:01:00,300
and you're probably already feeling the power spike

26
00:01:00,800 --> 00:01:02,433
you can't run your EBF full time

27
00:01:02,466 --> 00:01:03,300
make that a goal

28
00:01:03,500 --> 00:01:06,300
and don't be afraid to use multiple types of power production to make it happen

29
00:01:06,600 --> 00:01:08,100
and keep the aluminum cranking

30
00:01:08,266 --> 00:01:10,333
by using the alumina and cryolite recipe

31
00:01:11,100 --> 00:01:12,200
and don't forget steel

32
00:01:12,933 --> 00:01:15,933
as usual, "you're gonna hate this" quest unlock the meat of the chapter

33
00:01:16,100 --> 00:01:18,866
and let that be your reminder to get familiar with conveyors and pumps

34
00:01:19,233 --> 00:01:21,066
the chemical lines you'll be diving into in MV

35
00:01:21,066 --> 00:01:23,066
are gonna require cell management for fluids

36
00:01:23,133 --> 00:01:27,066
and you're probably at the point where upgrading the covers on your power system makes sense for transport speed

37
00:01:27,800 --> 00:01:30,100
the flawless emerald for the sensor might be a bit of a trick

38
00:01:30,266 --> 00:01:32,300
but enough poking around the nether should get you a few

39
00:01:32,300 --> 00:01:33,533
or you can look into sifting

40
00:01:33,866 --> 00:01:36,233
for the most part, MV is about upgrades

41
00:01:36,333 --> 00:01:39,033
either for speed, bonus output or cost

42
00:01:39,666 --> 00:01:41,866
after you get the extruder for more efficient rod production

43
00:01:41,866 --> 00:01:44,100
the next thing on the list is probably the electrolyzer

44
00:01:44,333 --> 00:01:45,733
you actually can make it right away

45
00:01:45,733 --> 00:01:47,600
without getting that "you're gonna hate this" quest

46
00:01:47,600 --> 00:01:49,866
but the extruder will help you keep scaling towards your power plan

47
00:01:49,866 --> 00:01:52,100
so it's probably six one way, half dozen the other

48
00:01:52,266 --> 00:01:53,333
you need it all either way

49
00:01:54,200 --> 00:01:57,533
speaking of, there's some crossover dependencies inside the MV chapter

50
00:01:57,533 --> 00:01:59,066
but you can approach it with different paths

51
00:01:59,066 --> 00:02:00,033
this is just one

52
00:02:00,400 --> 00:02:01,833
and to be fair to the electrolyzer

53
00:02:01,833 --> 00:02:03,666
it's probably the most important machine of the tier

54
00:02:04,400 --> 00:02:06,933
to start you'll probably just be slamming different dust through the machine

55
00:02:06,933 --> 00:02:08,400
and routing the outputs to drawers

56
00:02:08,700 --> 00:02:10,033
that'll work just fine to begin

57
00:02:10,200 --> 00:02:12,066
just make sure you have enough drawers for all the outputs 

58
00:02:12,066 --> 00:02:13,833
and you're storing all the fluid outputs

59
00:02:13,833 --> 00:02:15,200
and have a way to avoid water

60
00:02:16,266 --> 00:02:18,200
you'll need to electrolyze ruby dust for chrome

61
00:02:18,500 --> 00:02:20,900
find one with redstone ore veins and a lot of it

62
00:02:21,133 --> 00:02:23,700
electrolyzing sodalite is great for starting silicon and sodium

63
00:02:23,700 --> 00:02:25,233
and stockpiling aluminum dust

64
00:02:25,266 --> 00:02:26,900
and salt is ideal for chlorine

65
00:02:27,500 --> 00:02:29,433
but that hardened clay biome you found ages ago

66
00:02:29,433 --> 00:02:31,533
is about to become critically important

67
00:02:31,900 --> 00:02:33,333
even if only for a short while

68
00:02:33,866 --> 00:02:36,000
macerate it, then electrolyze the clay dust

69
00:02:36,000 --> 00:02:39,433
for tons of aluminum, sodium, lithium and silicon dioxide

70
00:02:40,266 --> 00:02:43,233
the silicon dioxide can be sent through a chemical reactor with magnesium

71
00:02:43,266 --> 00:02:45,266
which you can get by centrifuging marble dust

72
00:02:45,433 --> 00:02:47,066
to get raw silicon dust

73
00:02:48,733 --> 00:02:52,000
this is 100 percent going to be worth automating end to end

74
00:02:52,300 --> 00:02:55,100
the magnesium can be recycled, also in an electrolyzer

75
00:02:55,100 --> 00:02:56,833
to get the original magnesium back

76
00:02:56,933 --> 00:02:59,533
so the only input item is the silicon dioxide dust

77
00:02:59,933 --> 00:03:02,400
the magnesium input is what's called a closed loop

78
00:03:02,733 --> 00:03:05,100
meaning the same system that produces your ideal output

79
00:03:05,100 --> 00:03:07,133
also produces more of your input items

80
00:03:07,500 --> 00:03:09,433
you want to look for these as often as you can

81
00:03:10,266 --> 00:03:13,300
there are many other ways to get silicon dioxide too

82
00:03:13,666 --> 00:03:15,066
most players are going to want glass

83
00:03:15,066 --> 00:03:17,500
so a little setup to turn cobblestone into glass dust

84
00:03:17,500 --> 00:03:18,733
some being turned into glass

85
00:03:18,733 --> 00:03:20,100
and some into silicon dioxide

86
00:03:20,100 --> 00:03:21,100
will make it renewable

87
00:03:21,300 --> 00:03:23,466
another thing you'll want to be looking for as often as you can

88
00:03:23,833 --> 00:03:26,233
and you plug it into the same setup you're using for clay dust

89
00:03:27,433 --> 00:03:29,300
there are several use cases for raw silicon

90
00:03:29,533 --> 00:03:32,333
but for now the most important one is silicon solar grade dust

91
00:03:33,033 --> 00:03:34,233
there are two paths to making it

92
00:03:34,233 --> 00:03:36,000
and both have closed loop input items

93
00:03:36,000 --> 00:03:37,833
making raw silicon dust the only input

94
00:03:38,433 --> 00:03:41,100
the tetrachloride route is a little bit easier for cell management

95
00:03:41,100 --> 00:03:43,400
but it does take an extra machine to get the chlorine back

96
00:03:44,600 --> 00:03:47,733
the trichlorethylene route doesn't have any extra byproduct recycling

97
00:03:47,733 --> 00:03:48,933
but only deals with fluids

98
00:03:48,933 --> 00:03:50,600
so cell management can be tricky

99
00:03:51,066 --> 00:03:51,700
either way

100
00:03:51,700 --> 00:03:53,400
start working towards a full drawer of the stuff

101
00:03:53,400 --> 00:03:54,833
and be ready for a lot more

102
00:03:55,800 --> 00:03:59,000
while your SSG stacks up it's time to pivot to plastics

103
00:03:59,300 --> 00:04:01,466
polyethylene is one that has a ton of uses early

104
00:04:01,633 --> 00:04:04,900
from cheaper circuit components to EnderIO conduits and many more

105
00:04:05,400 --> 00:04:07,033
just like there are new circuits in every tier

106
00:04:07,033 --> 00:04:08,300
there are new plastics too

107
00:04:08,533 --> 00:04:10,000
they're usually not required right away

108
00:04:10,000 --> 00:04:11,466
and polyethylene is no different

109
00:04:11,666 --> 00:04:14,100
you can get the HV circuits at the end of the chapter without it

110
00:04:14,600 --> 00:04:17,733
and the circuit boards the quest line calls out aren't actually needed until HV

111
00:04:18,266 --> 00:04:21,466
but not having it would make the next part a lot more expensive

112
00:04:23,066 --> 00:04:24,533
if you didn't notice during the LV tier

113
00:04:24,533 --> 00:04:27,600
there are a couple different types of circuit components that can work to make each circuit

114
00:04:27,933 --> 00:04:29,200
the recipe will rotate through them

115
00:04:29,200 --> 00:04:30,666
so you can see everything that works

116
00:04:31,066 --> 00:04:33,200
there are also multiple ways to make each component

117
00:04:33,266 --> 00:04:35,866
each with a higher return in exchange for a better material

118
00:04:36,300 --> 00:04:39,233
TLDR: make the best thing you can afford, always

119
00:04:39,933 --> 00:04:42,900
staying in supply of tantalum at this point probably isn't realistic

120
00:04:42,900 --> 00:04:43,933
or possible at all

121
00:04:44,066 --> 00:04:45,333
and as the quest book suggests

122
00:04:45,333 --> 00:04:48,200
the resistor is probably the only upgrade you can afford right now

123
00:04:48,300 --> 00:04:49,233
but they're worth it

124
00:04:49,233 --> 00:04:50,600
even with the electrum recipe

125
00:04:52,100 --> 00:04:54,700
you can also view the entire circuitry with this little button

126
00:04:55,133 --> 00:04:55,933
there's a lot here

127
00:04:55,933 --> 00:04:56,533
and honestly

128
00:04:56,533 --> 00:04:58,800
this is most useful for illustrating two things

129
00:04:59,400 --> 00:05:01,733
the first is the order of upgrades per tier of circuit

130
00:05:01,733 --> 00:05:02,866
along the horizontal

131
00:05:03,133 --> 00:05:04,633
from most to least expensive

132
00:05:04,633 --> 00:05:05,466
or set another way

133
00:05:05,466 --> 00:05:06,500
from the first ones you'll make

134
00:05:06,500 --> 00:05:07,666
to the last ones you'll make

135
00:05:08,500 --> 00:05:09,266
and the other is

136
00:05:09,266 --> 00:05:11,633
which circuit boards are required for which level of circuit

137
00:05:11,633 --> 00:05:12,600
along the vertical

138
00:05:12,800 --> 00:05:14,466
from the lowest tier to the highest tier

139
00:05:15,066 --> 00:05:16,266
it can be a little confusing

140
00:05:16,266 --> 00:05:17,233
so to simplify

141
00:05:17,233 --> 00:05:18,266
in order to advance

142
00:05:18,266 --> 00:05:22,066
you'll need to make preposterously expensive mainframe circuits using cheap boards

143
00:05:22,266 --> 00:05:24,066
and to unlock the cheaper circuit recipes

144
00:05:24,066 --> 00:05:25,700
you'll need to unlock better boards

145
00:05:28,733 --> 00:05:31,533
so, now you know why you don't want to delay your chemistry

146
00:05:31,933 --> 00:05:34,800
it's going to get ridiculously expensive to proceed if you do

147
00:05:35,233 --> 00:05:37,100
the next step is actually doing it

148
00:05:37,633 --> 00:05:39,333
making polyethylene is the easy part

149
00:05:39,433 --> 00:05:41,000
you just mix ethylene with oxygen

150
00:05:41,400 --> 00:05:42,666
you already know how to make oxygen

151
00:05:42,666 --> 00:05:43,533
so if you need more

152
00:05:43,533 --> 00:05:45,400
give polyethylene its own oxygen setup

153
00:05:45,833 --> 00:05:47,866
it's a little early to share fluid setups easily

154
00:05:47,866 --> 00:05:49,266
so if you're having trouble doing it

155
00:05:49,333 --> 00:05:50,133
don't bother

156
00:05:51,400 --> 00:05:52,466
you can take it over too

157
00:05:52,466 --> 00:05:55,300
but if you don't have enough chores with all the mining and ore processing you've been doing

158
00:05:55,300 --> 00:05:56,333
I'd be surprised

159
00:05:56,666 --> 00:05:58,633
surely you haven't forgotten about mining, right?

160
00:05:59,400 --> 00:06:00,266
we'll get back to that

161
00:06:00,533 --> 00:06:01,933
for now, ethylene

162
00:06:02,833 --> 00:06:04,866
like most things there are a number of ways to get it

163
00:06:05,133 --> 00:06:08,533
and the way you choose will probably be connected to your power system choice

164
00:06:09,500 --> 00:06:10,233
at this point

165
00:06:10,233 --> 00:06:11,466
things are getting pretty busy

166
00:06:11,600 --> 00:06:12,600
so if you need to take a beat here

167
00:06:12,600 --> 00:06:14,266
and get organized with your power system

168
00:06:14,266 --> 00:06:15,133
definitely do

169
00:06:15,233 --> 00:06:18,200
check out episode 5 if you missed it for more details on the options

170
00:06:18,533 --> 00:06:19,433
the good news is

171
00:06:19,433 --> 00:06:21,133
your silicone is probably built up enough by now

172
00:06:21,133 --> 00:06:23,400
that you can start thinking about the MV Energy hatch

173
00:06:24,666 --> 00:06:26,500
stock back up on gallium and arsenic

174
00:06:26,800 --> 00:06:27,933
it's still a bit painful

175
00:06:27,933 --> 00:06:29,033
but MV miners are great

176
00:06:29,200 --> 00:06:31,066
and blast furnace your way to some boules

177
00:06:31,600 --> 00:06:33,600
this is a long smelting operation

178
00:06:33,600 --> 00:06:35,200
so make sure you don't run out of fuel

179
00:06:35,900 --> 00:06:37,866
grab the MV cutting machine and Laser Engraver too

180
00:06:38,266 --> 00:06:43,200
the thaumcraft shards you grab for magic can be made into the Tera lenses and Ignis lenses if you struggled for emerald and ruby

181
00:06:43,300 --> 00:06:44,600
but for the RAM you need later

182
00:06:44,600 --> 00:06:46,133
you'll have to hunt down sapphires

183
00:06:46,533 --> 00:06:48,000
for now grab the Terra lens

184
00:06:48,000 --> 00:06:50,800
and make low power ICs and the MV Energy hatch

185
00:06:51,833 --> 00:06:53,600
if you manage to get the other ones too

186
00:06:53,633 --> 00:06:56,533
take advantage of cheaper LV and MV circuits starting right away

187
00:06:56,866 --> 00:06:58,666
feel free to upgrade the EBF now too

188
00:06:58,666 --> 00:07:00,533
but definitely upgrade your power system

189
00:07:02,466 --> 00:07:03,933
the EBF will be relevant soon

190
00:07:04,000 --> 00:07:06,266
but if you're opting for steam or benzene for long term power

191
00:07:06,266 --> 00:07:08,333
what you need at the moment is the pyrolysis oven

192
00:07:09,400 --> 00:07:10,933
get your farms an oven set for power

193
00:07:10,933 --> 00:07:13,933
then divert some wood into a secondary pyrolysis to make wood gas

194
00:07:13,933 --> 00:07:15,000
using circuit 5

195
00:07:15,033 --> 00:07:16,900
and don't forget the nitrogen for efficiency

196
00:07:17,500 --> 00:07:19,433
then distill the wood gas for ethylene

197
00:07:19,733 --> 00:07:20,333
easy peasy

198
00:07:20,333 --> 00:07:21,866
ready to mix with oxygen

199
00:07:23,433 --> 00:07:25,700
if you opted for fuel like I did in my main world

200
00:07:25,700 --> 00:07:29,600
the straightest line to ethylene for now is to divert some of the light fuel into a chemical reactor

201
00:07:29,633 --> 00:07:31,900
mix with steam for severely steamed light fuel

202
00:07:31,900 --> 00:07:33,200
and distill for ethylene

203
00:07:33,833 --> 00:07:37,100
you can complicate this a bit by making lightly steamed light fuel instead

204
00:07:37,133 --> 00:07:38,800
and distilling into naphtha first

205
00:07:38,800 --> 00:07:40,066
then steaming it again

206
00:07:40,066 --> 00:07:42,733
and distilling the naphtha into ethylene for a better return

207
00:07:43,033 --> 00:07:44,500
but if you're going oil long term

208
00:07:44,600 --> 00:07:47,200
it might be better to wait for the distillation tower to do that

209
00:07:48,000 --> 00:07:50,233
even if you got crazy and went bio-diesel for power

210
00:07:50,233 --> 00:07:52,700
there's a way to get ethylene through ethanol and sulfuric acid

211
00:07:52,833 --> 00:07:53,833
but like everything else

212
00:07:53,833 --> 00:07:57,233
it's a big investment that's only worth it if the plans all align for you

213
00:07:58,233 --> 00:08:00,200
you can also get into EnderIO now

214
00:08:00,533 --> 00:08:01,433
we aren't going to cover it here

215
00:08:01,433 --> 00:08:03,633
because the quest book does a great job of walking you through

216
00:08:03,700 --> 00:08:04,733
but I'll say this

217
00:08:04,733 --> 00:08:07,800
item conduits with item filters will be life changing

218
00:08:08,933 --> 00:08:10,533
now, with power well under control

219
00:08:10,533 --> 00:08:11,666
and polyethylene in hand

220
00:08:11,666 --> 00:08:13,100
it's time to get back to the EBF

221
00:08:13,633 --> 00:08:15,133
double up on MV Energy hatches

222
00:08:15,133 --> 00:08:16,633
and get that bad boy to HV

223
00:08:16,700 --> 00:08:18,400
and get ready to roll some coal

224
00:08:19,200 --> 00:08:21,633
you got plenty of chrome by now from all the electrolyzing too

225
00:08:21,833 --> 00:08:23,066
oh you forgot about that

226
00:08:23,400 --> 00:08:25,033
back to the mines with you immediately

227
00:08:25,400 --> 00:08:28,266
anyway mix up some kanthal dust in your new MV mixer

228
00:08:28,266 --> 00:08:29,266
and get to smelting

229
00:08:30,533 --> 00:08:31,700
to cool the hot ingots

230
00:08:31,700 --> 00:08:33,433
you'll need a chemical bath with some coolant in

231
00:08:34,266 --> 00:08:35,933
you make the coolant with water and lapis dust

232
00:08:35,933 --> 00:08:37,733
which means it's effectively free

233
00:08:38,300 --> 00:08:39,700
I might catch some heat for this one

234
00:08:39,700 --> 00:08:42,933
but I don't think it's worth using the tank and fan to recycle the coolant

235
00:08:43,433 --> 00:08:44,533
just make the distilled water

236
00:08:44,533 --> 00:08:45,833
and max out a tank of the stuff

237
00:08:46,133 --> 00:08:47,533
with 128 buckets

238
00:08:47,533 --> 00:08:49,200
you can cool over 500 ingots

239
00:08:49,200 --> 00:08:52,433
which was way more than I personally needed before crafting the vacuum freezer

240
00:08:53,466 --> 00:08:54,833
with the basic cooling system

241
00:08:54,833 --> 00:08:55,933
some kanthal coils

242
00:08:55,933 --> 00:08:57,866
which by the way this time require mica

243
00:08:57,866 --> 00:09:00,300
so if you cheaped out last time, get the prospecting

244
00:09:00,800 --> 00:09:02,833
you can start cooking and cooling SSG ingots

245
00:09:02,866 --> 00:09:04,900
and start making HV circuits at last

246
00:09:04,900 --> 00:09:07,000
the very very expensive way

247
00:09:08,000 --> 00:09:11,000
and finally the HV metal, stainless steel

248
00:09:11,300 --> 00:09:12,533
you're probably hurting for chrome

249
00:09:12,533 --> 00:09:13,700
and that's totally normal

250
00:09:13,700 --> 00:09:14,700
so get back to the mines

251
00:09:14,700 --> 00:09:18,233
or start centrifuging that outrageous backlog of redstone for extra ruby dust

252
00:09:18,300 --> 00:09:20,933
and power the setup using all that mercury and an acid generator

253
00:09:21,466 --> 00:09:23,800
it was exactly at this point in my own journey that

254
00:09:23,800 --> 00:09:27,233
I pivoted into magic and bees to solve for some of these trickier resources

255
00:09:27,500 --> 00:09:29,333
there are other ways to approach getting ruby

256
00:09:29,466 --> 00:09:30,666
and if you're having serious trouble

257
00:09:30,666 --> 00:09:32,500
definitely consider using the ruby juice

258
00:09:32,733 --> 00:09:34,433
the only trick is the hydrochloric acid

259
00:09:34,533 --> 00:09:36,900
but let's not pretend like you have enough ruby to need it infinitely

260
00:09:37,933 --> 00:09:40,433
and anyway, match up as much stainless as you can afford

261
00:09:40,733 --> 00:09:42,866
you'll be making some more multi blocks in the next tier

262
00:09:42,900 --> 00:09:44,066
and they're expensive

263
00:09:45,433 --> 00:09:47,633
and so it was that you were ready for HV

264
00:09:48,033 --> 00:09:48,833
how about that

265
00:09:49,800 --> 00:09:51,400
there are some things we glossed over though

266
00:09:51,500 --> 00:09:52,900
so let's do some highlights

267
00:09:53,933 --> 00:09:56,433
EnderIO has some amazing things to offer

268
00:09:56,500 --> 00:09:57,933
from easy travel around your base

269
00:09:57,933 --> 00:09:59,633
to automated mob spawning and killing

270
00:10:00,066 --> 00:10:02,000
it's different in GTNH, naturally

271
00:10:02,000 --> 00:10:03,066
but still amazing

272
00:10:03,333 --> 00:10:05,700
and the dark steel chests are needed for the compressed chest

273
00:10:05,700 --> 00:10:07,933
godliest of all for purposes of mining

274
00:10:08,466 --> 00:10:10,400
polyvinyl Chloride is a little French for now

275
00:10:10,400 --> 00:10:14,066
but super worth having around as you start making improved circuit components with your polyethylene

276
00:10:14,466 --> 00:10:15,833
and make straight out of pipes

277
00:10:16,900 --> 00:10:19,600
the prospecting tool is a gift from Greg himself

278
00:10:19,733 --> 00:10:21,733
no more digging down to check ore veins

279
00:10:23,200 --> 00:10:25,233
The World Accelerator is an incredibly useful

280
00:10:25,233 --> 00:10:29,500
if equally power hungry little block that speeds up the tick rate of blocks and entities around it

281
00:10:30,033 --> 00:10:32,266
void upgrades keep your automated systems moving

282
00:10:32,266 --> 00:10:33,400
especially power

283
00:10:34,233 --> 00:10:37,466
super chests, for massive storage capacity of single items

284
00:10:38,400 --> 00:10:41,333
transporters, for close range item and fluid transport

285
00:10:41,800 --> 00:10:43,433
so many goodies to enjoy

286
00:10:43,633 --> 00:10:45,833
and one big giant gotcha

287
00:10:46,600 --> 00:10:48,300
since you don't need those circuit boards now

288
00:10:48,333 --> 00:10:51,533
it can be easy to ignore the iron III Chloride or the sodium persulfate

289
00:10:52,066 --> 00:10:53,866
don't overlook this

290
00:10:54,000 --> 00:10:55,866
you need giant quantities

291
00:10:56,033 --> 00:10:58,066
so you either need to think hard about sulfuric acid

292
00:10:58,066 --> 00:10:59,666
or you need to think hard about chlorine

293
00:11:00,233 --> 00:11:01,066
it's not urgent

294
00:11:01,066 --> 00:11:02,866
but once you start needing it during HV

295
00:11:03,000 --> 00:11:05,133
you'll hit a brick wall if you can't make quite a lot

296
00:11:05,533 --> 00:11:06,600
you might have also noticed

297
00:11:06,600 --> 00:11:08,733
there weren't as many single block machine quests this time

298
00:11:08,733 --> 00:11:09,933
get used to that

299
00:11:10,066 --> 00:11:10,800
but don't forget

300
00:11:10,800 --> 00:11:13,033
every tier has new additions of all the machines

301
00:11:13,033 --> 00:11:14,033
and they're all better

302
00:11:14,233 --> 00:11:15,033
other than that

303
00:11:15,200 --> 00:11:16,266
be ready for the big one

304
00:11:16,833 --> 00:11:18,800
new multi blocks, the clean room

305
00:11:18,800 --> 00:11:19,600
the moon

306
00:11:19,600 --> 00:11:20,400
titanium

307
00:11:20,666 --> 00:11:22,100
applied energistics

308
00:11:22,866 --> 00:11:24,333
are you really a beginner anymore

309
00:11:24,833 --> 00:11:26,233
I guess we'll find out in HV

310
00:11:26,733 --> 00:11:28,066
see you there for episode 8

311
00:00:00,333 --> 00:00:01,800
现在你是真的开干了

312
00:00:02,433 --> 00:00:03,700
你不只有干劲

313
00:00:03,900 --> 00:00:05,233
你有目标

314
00:00:05,466 --> 00:00:06,600
电力系统

315
00:00:06,733 --> 00:00:08,133
还有魔法药剂

316
00:00:08,200 --> 00:00:09,800
再加上MV阶段一路顺风

317
00:00:10,533 --> 00:00:12,700
但是任务书吓到你了

318
00:00:13,133 --> 00:00:14,866
事情很快就会变得更复杂

319
00:00:15,466 --> 00:00:16,400
化学线

320
00:00:16,400 --> 00:00:17,866
多步自动化

321
00:00:17,866 --> 00:00:19,233
新的模组和金属

322
00:00:19,333 --> 00:00:21,500
以及你从未见过的全新电路元件

323
00:00:22,000 --> 00:00:22,933
这到底是啥？

324
00:00:23,700 --> 00:00:24,533
格雷格科技

325
00:00:24,533 --> 00:00:25,333
就是它

326
00:00:25,733 --> 00:00:29,066
欢迎回到GregTech New Horizons初学者指南

327
00:00:29,066 --> 00:00:30,400
今天我们升级

328
00:00:30,733 --> 00:00:32,400
如果你想让事情更上一层楼

329
00:00:32,400 --> 00:00:33,666
你来对地方了

330
00:00:33,666 --> 00:00:34,700
这是第7集

331
00:00:35,300 --> 00:00:36,100
MV

332
00:00:52,800 --> 00:00:54,333
这次的开场白不多

333
00:00:54,800 --> 00:00:56,266
你应该为你的动力系统设定一个目标

334
00:00:56,266 --> 00:00:58,200
也许还有一些你已经知道你想拿的好东西

335
00:00:58,333 --> 00:01:00,300
你可能已经感受到用电压力暴涨了

336
00:01:00,800 --> 00:01:02,433
你的EBF还没法全时运行

337
00:01:02,466 --> 00:01:03,300
把它作为一个目标

338
00:01:03,500 --> 00:01:06,300
不要害怕使用多种类型的电力生产来实现它

339
00:01:06,600 --> 00:01:08,100
同时继续稳定量产铝

340
00:01:08,266 --> 00:01:10,333
用氧化铝+冰晶石那条配方线

341
00:01:11,100 --> 00:01:12,200
别忘了钢铁

342
00:01:12,933 --> 00:01:15,933
像往常一样，“你会讨厌这个”的任务解锁了这一章的内容

343
00:01:16,100 --> 00:01:18,866
也提醒你尽快熟悉传送带和泵

344
00:01:19,233 --> 00:01:21,066
你在MV会深入的化工产线

345
00:01:21,066 --> 00:01:23,066
会需要做流体单元管理

346
00:01:23,133 --> 00:01:27,066
你可能正处于升级电力系统覆盖板来提速运输就很有必要的地步

347
00:01:27,800 --> 00:01:30,100
传感器要的无瑕祖母绿可能有点麻烦

348
00:01:30,266 --> 00:01:32,300
不过在下界多逛一逛通常能搞到一些

349
00:01:32,300 --> 00:01:33,533
或者你也可以考虑筛矿

350
00:01:33,866 --> 00:01:36,233
在大多数情况下，MV是关于升级的

351
00:01:36,333 --> 00:01:39,033
无论是速度、额外产出还是成本

352
00:01:39,666 --> 00:01:41,866
获得更高效的棒材生产的挤出机后

353
00:01:41,866 --> 00:01:44,100
名单上的下一件事可能是电解槽

354
00:01:44,333 --> 00:01:45,733
其实你可以立刻就做。

355
00:01:45,733 --> 00:01:47,600
没有得到“你会讨厌这个”的任务

356
00:01:47,600 --> 00:01:49,866
但挤出机会更有助于你继续扩建供电方案

357
00:01:49,866 --> 00:01:52,100
所以两条路都差不多

358
00:01:52,266 --> 00:01:53,333
反正这些机器你都得做

359
00:01:54,200 --> 00:01:57,533
顺带一提，MV章节内部有一些交叉依赖

360
00:01:57,533 --> 00:01:59,066
不过你可以走不同路线推进

361
00:01:59,066 --> 00:02:00,033
这只是一个

362
00:02:00,400 --> 00:02:01,833
为了对电解槽公平起见

363
00:02:01,833 --> 00:02:03,666
这可能是这层最重要的机器

364
00:02:04,400 --> 00:02:06,933
开局你大概率就是把各种粉往机器里塞

365
00:02:06,933 --> 00:02:08,400
并把产物分流到抽屉

366
00:02:08,700 --> 00:02:10,033
这样起步完全够用

367
00:02:10,200 --> 00:02:12,066
只要确保你有足够的抽屉来放所有的输出

368
00:02:12,066 --> 00:02:13,833
你储存了所有的液体输出

369
00:02:13,833 --> 00:02:15,200
并且要有处理水副产物的办法

370
00:02:16,266 --> 00:02:18,200
你需要电解红宝石粉来获得铬

371
00:02:18,500 --> 00:02:20,900
去找红石矿脉并大量开采

372
00:02:21,133 --> 00:02:23,700
电解方钠石很适合前期启动硅和钠

373
00:02:23,700 --> 00:02:25,233
并储存铝粉

374
00:02:25,266 --> 00:02:26,900
盐是氯的理想选择

375
00:02:27,500 --> 00:02:29,433
但是你很久以前发现的硬化黏土生物群系

376
00:02:29,433 --> 00:02:31,533
即将变得至关重要

377
00:02:31,900 --> 00:02:33,333
即使只有很短的一段时间

378
00:02:33,866 --> 00:02:36,000
先粉碎再电解黏土粉

379
00:02:36,000 --> 00:02:39,433
能产出大量铝、钠、锂和二氧化硅

380
00:02:40,266 --> 00:02:43,233
二氧化硅可以和镁一起通过化学反应器

381
00:02:43,266 --> 00:02:45,266
你可以通过离心大理石灰尘来获得

382
00:02:45,433 --> 00:02:47,066
得到粗硅粉

383
00:02:48,733 --> 00:02:52,000
这是100%值得端到端自动化的

384
00:02:52,300 --> 00:02:55,100
镁可以回收，也可以在电解槽中回收

385
00:02:55,100 --> 00:02:56,833
把原来的镁拿回来

386
00:02:56,933 --> 00:02:59,533
所以唯一净输入是二氧化硅粉尘

387
00:02:59,933 --> 00:03:02,400
镁的输入就是所谓的闭环

388
00:03:02,733 --> 00:03:05,100
这意味着产生理想输出的相同系统

389
00:03:05,100 --> 00:03:07,133
还会产生更多的输入材料

390
00:03:07,500 --> 00:03:09,433
你想尽可能经常地寻找这些

391
00:03:10,266 --> 00:03:13,300
还有许多其他方法可以获得二氧化硅

392
00:03:13,666 --> 00:03:15,066
大多数玩家会想要玻璃

393
00:03:15,066 --> 00:03:17,500
所以把圆石打成玻璃粉的小装置

394
00:03:17,500 --> 00:03:18,733
有些被变成了玻璃

395
00:03:18,733 --> 00:03:20,100
一部分再转成二氧化硅

396
00:03:20,100 --> 00:03:21,100
将使其可再生

397
00:03:21,300 --> 00:03:23,466
这也是你应尽量经常寻找的套路

398
00:03:23,833 --> 00:03:26,233
可以直接接进你做黏土粉那套系统

399
00:03:27,433 --> 00:03:29,300
粗硅有不少用途

400
00:03:29,533 --> 00:03:32,333
但目前最重要的是太阳能级硅粉

401
00:03:33,033 --> 00:03:34,233
有两条路可以走

402
00:03:34,233 --> 00:03:36,000
并且都有闭环输入材料

403
00:03:36,000 --> 00:03:37,833
使原始硅粉成为唯一的输入

404
00:03:38,433 --> 00:03:41,100
四氯化硅路线对细胞管理更容易一点

405
00:03:41,100 --> 00:03:43,400
但是需要一台额外的机器才能把氯拿回来

406
00:03:44,600 --> 00:03:47,733
三氯乙烯路线没有任何额外的副产品回收

407
00:03:47,733 --> 00:03:48,933
但只处理液体

408
00:03:48,933 --> 00:03:50,600
所以细胞管理可能很棘手

409
00:03:51,066 --> 00:03:51,700
不管怎样

410
00:03:51,700 --> 00:03:53,400
开始朝着满满一抽屉的东西努力

411
00:03:53,400 --> 00:03:54,833
并为更多做好准备

412
00:03:55,800 --> 00:03:59,000
当你的SSG堆积起来时，是时候转向塑料了

413
00:03:59,300 --> 00:04:01,466
聚乙烯在早期有很多用途。

414
00:04:01,633 --> 00:04:04,900
从更便宜的电路组件到EnderIO导管等等

415
00:04:05,400 --> 00:04:07,033
就像每层都有新电路一样

416
00:04:07,033 --> 00:04:08,300
还有新的塑料

417
00:04:08,533 --> 00:04:10,000
它们通常不会立刻就要用到

418
00:04:10,000 --> 00:04:11,466
聚乙烯也不例外

419
00:04:11,666 --> 00:04:14,100
你可以在没有它的情况下得到本章末尾的高压电路

420
00:04:14,600 --> 00:04:17,733
任务线点名的电路板其实到HV才真正需要

421
00:04:18,266 --> 00:04:21,466
但是没有它会让下一部分更贵。

422
00:04:23,066 --> 00:04:24,533
如果你在LV层没注意到

423
00:04:24,533 --> 00:04:27,600
有几个不同类型的电路组件可以工作，使每个电路

424
00:04:27,933 --> 00:04:29,200
配方会在这些选项间轮换

425
00:04:29,200 --> 00:04:30,666
这样你就可以看到所有有效的东西。

426
00:04:31,066 --> 00:04:33,200
也有多种方法来制作每个组件

427
00:04:33,266 --> 00:04:35,866
每一个都有更高的回报以换取更好的材料

428
00:04:36,300 --> 00:04:39,233
一句话：永远做你当前负担得起的最好方案

429
00:04:39,933 --> 00:04:42,900
在这一点上保持钽的供应可能是不现实的

430
00:04:42,900 --> 00:04:43,933
或者根本不可能

431
00:04:44,066 --> 00:04:45,333
正如任务书所说的

432
00:04:45,333 --> 00:04:48,200
电阻器可能是您现在唯一能负担得起的升级

433
00:04:48,300 --> 00:04:49,233
但它们是值得的

434
00:04:49,233 --> 00:04:50,600
即使是琥珀金配方也值得做

435
00:04:52,100 --> 00:04:54,700
你也可以点这个小按钮查看完整电路树

436
00:04:55,133 --> 00:04:55,933
这里有很多

437
00:04:55,933 --> 00:04:56,533
老实说

438
00:04:56,533 --> 00:04:58,800
这对说明两件事最有用

439
00:04:59,400 --> 00:05:01,733
第一个是每层电路的升级顺序

440
00:05:01,733 --> 00:05:02,866
沿水平方向

441
00:05:03,133 --> 00:05:04,633
从最贵到最便宜

442
00:05:04,633 --> 00:05:05,466
换个说法

443
00:05:05,466 --> 00:05:06,500
从你要做的第一个开始

444
00:05:06,500 --> 00:05:07,666
到你要做的最后一个

445
00:05:08,500 --> 00:05:09,266
另一个是

446
00:05:09,266 --> 00:05:11,633
哪个级别的电路需要哪些电路板

447
00:05:11,633 --> 00:05:12,600
沿垂直方向

448
00:05:12,800 --> 00:05:14,466
从最低层到最高层

449
00:05:15,066 --> 00:05:16,266
这可能有点令人困惑

450
00:05:16,266 --> 00:05:17,233
所以为了简化

451
00:05:17,233 --> 00:05:18,266
为了前进

452
00:05:18,266 --> 00:05:22,066
你得先用便宜板子去做贵得离谱的主电路

453
00:05:22,266 --> 00:05:24,066
并解锁更便宜的电路配方

454
00:05:24,066 --> 00:05:25,700
你需要解锁更好的板子

455
00:05:28,733 --> 00:05:31,533
现在你知道为什么不想耽误化学反应了吧

456
00:05:31,933 --> 00:05:34,800
如果你这样做，继续下去会变得非常昂贵

457
00:05:35,233 --> 00:05:37,100
下一步就是真正去做。

458
00:05:37,633 --> 00:05:39,333
制造聚乙烯是最简单的部分

459
00:05:39,433 --> 00:05:41,000
你只要把乙烯和氧气混合

460
00:05:41,400 --> 00:05:42,666
你已经知道怎么制造氧气了

461
00:05:42,666 --> 00:05:43,533
所以如果你需要更多

462
00:05:43,533 --> 00:05:45,400
给聚乙烯自己的氧气装置

463
00:05:45,833 --> 00:05:47,866
这个阶段还不太适合轻松共用流体系统

464
00:05:47,866 --> 00:05:49,266
所以如果你做这件事有困难

465
00:05:49,333 --> 00:05:50,133
不用麻烦了

466
00:05:51,400 --> 00:05:52,466
你也可以先把这块放一放

467
00:05:52,466 --> 00:05:55,300
但是如果你没有足够的活儿来处理你一直在做的采矿和矿石加工

468
00:05:55,300 --> 00:05:56,333
我会惊讶的

469
00:05:56,666 --> 00:05:58,633
你肯定没有忘记采矿，对吧？

470
00:05:59,400 --> 00:06:00,266
我们回头再说

471
00:06:00,533 --> 00:06:01,933
现在是乙烯

472
00:06:02,833 --> 00:06:04,866
像大多数事情一样，有很多方法可以得到它

473
00:06:05,133 --> 00:06:08,533
您选择的方式可能与您的电力系统选择有关

474
00:06:09,500 --> 00:06:10,233
在这一点上

475
00:06:10,233 --> 00:06:11,466
事情越来越忙了

476
00:06:11,600 --> 00:06:12,600
所以如果你需要在这里休息一下

477
00:06:12,600 --> 00:06:14,266
用你的电力系统组织起来

478
00:06:14,266 --> 00:06:15,133
就这么做

479
00:06:15,233 --> 00:06:18,200
如果您错过了第5集，请查看第5集，了解有关选项的更多详细信息

480
00:06:18,533 --> 00:06:19,433
好消息是

481
00:06:19,433 --> 00:06:21,133
你的硅粉现在大概率已经攒得差不多了

482
00:06:21,133 --> 00:06:23,400
可以开始考虑做MV能源仓了

483
00:06:24,666 --> 00:06:26,500
把镓和砷再补一波库存

484
00:06:26,800 --> 00:06:27,933
还是有点疼

485
00:06:27,933 --> 00:06:29,033
不过MV矿机真的很好用。

486
00:06:29,200 --> 00:06:31,066
然后去高炉慢慢烧出几根晶锭。

487
00:06:31,600 --> 00:06:33,600
这是一个漫长的冶炼作业

488
00:06:33,600 --> 00:06:35,200
所以确保你没有用完燃料

489
00:06:35,900 --> 00:06:37,866
顺手把MV切割机和激光雕刻机也做了

490
00:06:38,266 --> 00:06:43,200
如果你祖母绿和红宝石不够，做魔法时拿到的神秘时代碎片可以做Terra和Ignis镜片

491
00:06:43,300 --> 00:06:44,600
但后面要做RAM的话

492
00:06:44,600 --> 00:06:46,133
你得去找蓝宝石

493
00:06:46,533 --> 00:06:48,000
现在，用地之魔晶透镜就行

494
00:06:48,000 --> 00:06:50,800
并制造低功耗IC和MV能源仓

495
00:06:51,833 --> 00:06:53,600
如果你也把其他几种镜片做出来了

496
00:06:53,633 --> 00:06:56,533
立即开始使用更便宜的LV和MV电路

497
00:06:56,866 --> 00:06:58,666
现在也可以随时升级EBF

498
00:06:58,666 --> 00:07:00,533
但一定要升级你的动力系统

499
00:07:02,466 --> 00:07:03,933
EBF很快就会再次成为重点

500
00:07:04,000 --> 00:07:06,266
但是如果你选择蒸汽或苯作为长期动力

501
00:07:06,266 --> 00:07:08,333
你现在需要的是热解炉

502
00:07:09,400 --> 00:07:10,933
先给农场配一套热解炉发电产线

503
00:07:10,933 --> 00:07:13,933
再分流一部分木头进第二套热解炉来产木炭气

504
00:07:13,933 --> 00:07:15,000
使用编程电路5

505
00:07:15,033 --> 00:07:16,900
别忘了氮气来提高效率

506
00:07:17,500 --> 00:07:19,433
然后把木炭气蒸馏出乙烯

507
00:07:19,733 --> 00:07:20,333
非常简单

508
00:07:20,333 --> 00:07:21,866
准备与氧气混合

509
00:07:23,433 --> 00:07:25,700
如果你像我一样选择柴油发电

510
00:07:25,700 --> 00:07:29,600
目前最直接的路线是将一些轻燃油转移到化学反应釜中

511
00:07:29,633 --> 00:07:31,900
用蒸汽裂化出重度蒸汽裂化轻燃油

512
00:07:31,900 --> 00:07:33,200
然后蒸馏出乙烯

513
00:07:33,833 --> 00:07:37,100
你也可以走轻度蒸汽裂化轻燃油这条更复杂的路线

514
00:07:37,133 --> 00:07:38,800
先蒸馏成石脑油

515
00:07:38,800 --> 00:07:40,066
然后用蒸汽裂化一次

516
00:07:40,066 --> 00:07:42,733
将石脑油蒸馏成乙烯能获得更多产物

517
00:07:43,033 --> 00:07:44,500
但是如果你要长期使用石油

518
00:07:44,600 --> 00:07:47,200
等有了蒸馏塔才这么做可能更好

519
00:07:48,000 --> 00:07:50,233
即使你疯了，用生物柴油发电

520
00:07:50,233 --> 00:07:52,700
可以通过乙醇和硫酸得到乙烯

521
00:07:52,833 --> 00:07:53,833
但就像其他一切一样

522
00:07:53,833 --> 00:07:57,233
这是一项巨大的投资，只有当计划都适合你时才值得

523
00:07:58,233 --> 00:08:00,200
现在你也可以开始发展EnderIO了

524
00:08:00,533 --> 00:08:01,433
这里我们就不展开讲了

525
00:08:01,433 --> 00:08:03,633
因为任务书引导得很好

526
00:08:03,700 --> 00:08:04,733
但我要说

527
00:08:04,733 --> 00:08:07,800
带过滤器的物品导管会彻底改变你的游戏体验

528
00:08:08,933 --> 00:08:10,533
现在，随着电力得到控制

529
00:08:10,533 --> 00:08:11,666
聚乙烯产线正常运转

530
00:08:11,666 --> 00:08:13,100
是时候回到EBF了

531
00:08:13,633 --> 00:08:15,133
装上两个MV能源仓

532
00:08:15,133 --> 00:08:16,633
把这大家升压到HV

533
00:08:16,700 --> 00:08:18,400
然后准备好开卷煤线（？）

534
00:08:19,200 --> 00:08:21,633
你现在也从电解中得到了足够的铬

535
00:08:21,833 --> 00:08:23,066
噢，你把这事忘了是吧

536
00:08:23,400 --> 00:08:25,033
马上回去挖矿吧

537
00:08:25,400 --> 00:08:28,266
总之在新的MV搅拌机里混合出坎塔尔粉

538
00:08:28,266 --> 00:08:29,266
然后开炉冶炼

539
00:08:30,533 --> 00:08:31,700
要给热锭降温

540
00:08:31,700 --> 00:08:33,433
你需要一个加冷却剂的化学浸洗机

541
00:08:34,266 --> 00:08:35,933
你用水和青金石粉做冷却剂

542
00:08:35,933 --> 00:08:37,733
这意味着它基本上是免费的

543
00:08:38,300 --> 00:08:39,700
这句可能会有点争议

544
00:08:39,700 --> 00:08:42,933
但我认为不值得用储罐和散热片来回收冷却液

545
00:08:43,433 --> 00:08:44,533
只有做点蒸馏水

546
00:08:44,533 --> 00:08:45,833
直接做一整罐冷却液

547
00:08:46,133 --> 00:08:47,533
128桶冷却液能冷却500多个锭

548
00:08:47,533 --> 00:08:49,200
（向上合并）

549
00:08:49,200 --> 00:08:52,433
这远超我自己在做出真空冷冻机之前的冷却需求

550
00:08:53,466 --> 00:08:54,833
有了这套基础冷却系统

551
00:08:54,833 --> 00:08:55,933
再做一些坎塔尔线圈

552
00:08:55,933 --> 00:08:57,866
顺便说一下，这次需要云母

553
00:08:57,866 --> 00:09:00,300
所以如果你上次做线圈偷懒了，现在就去探矿

554
00:09:00,800 --> 00:09:02,833
你就能开始烧制与冷却高速钢锭

555
00:09:02,866 --> 00:09:04,900
终于可以开始做HV电路

556
00:09:04,900 --> 00:09:07,000
以非常非常贵的方式做

557
00:09:08,000 --> 00:09:11,000
最后是HV金属：不锈钢

558
00:09:11,300 --> 00:09:12,533
你现在大概率很缺铬

559
00:09:12,533 --> 00:09:13,700
这完全正常

560
00:09:13,700 --> 00:09:14,700
所以回去挖矿吧

561
00:09:14,700 --> 00:09:18,233
或者把那塞满你仓库的红石拿去离心，获得额外的红宝石粉

562
00:09:18,300 --> 00:09:20,933
再用你攒的汞和酸性发电机给整套系统供电

563
00:09:21,466 --> 00:09:23,800
我就是在自己游戏的这个阶段

564
00:09:23,800 --> 00:09:27,233
转去做魔法和蜜蜂，来获取难搞的资源

565
00:09:27,500 --> 00:09:29,333
还有其他方法可以获得红宝石

566
00:09:29,466 --> 00:09:30,666
如果你遇到了严重的麻烦

567
00:09:30,666 --> 00:09:32,500
可以严肃考虑走红宝石汁路线

568
00:09:32,733 --> 00:09:34,433
唯一的麻烦的是盐酸

569
00:09:34,533 --> 00:09:36,900
但也别假装你红宝石自由到能够无限做红宝石汁

570
00:09:37,933 --> 00:09:40,433
总之，在你承受的范围内，多做些不锈钢

571
00:09:40,733 --> 00:09:42,866
下一个阶段你还会做更多的多方块机器

572
00:09:42,900 --> 00:09:44,066
而它们都很贵

573
00:09:45,433 --> 00:09:47,633
所以你已经准备好进入HV了

574
00:09:48,033 --> 00:09:48,833
怎么样，厉害吧

575
00:09:49,800 --> 00:09:51,400
不过有些事情我们忽略了

576
00:09:51,500 --> 00:09:52,900
所以来做个重点回顾

577
00:09:53,933 --> 00:09:56,433
EIO提供了一些惊人的东西

578
00:09:56,500 --> 00:09:57,933
从在基地内快速旅行

579
00:09:57,933 --> 00:09:59,633
到自动刷怪和杀怪

580
00:10:00,066 --> 00:10:02,000
自然地，它在GTNH中是不同的（？）

581
00:10:02,000 --> 00:10:03,066
但还是很牛逼

582
00:10:03,333 --> 00:10:05,700
压缩箱子需要先做玄钢箱子

583
00:10:05,700 --> 00:10:07,933
对采矿来说简直神中神

584
00:10:08,466 --> 00:10:10,400
现在做聚氯乙烯稍微有点早

585
00:10:10,400 --> 00:10:14,066
但当你开始用聚乙烯做改良电路组件时，它会非常值

586
00:10:14,466 --> 00:10:15,833
聚乙烯还能直接拿来做管道

587
00:10:16,900 --> 00:10:19,600
探矿仪是格雷自己送的礼物

588
00:10:19,733 --> 00:10:21,733
再也不用往下挖找矿脉了

589
00:10:23,200 --> 00:10:25,233
世界加速器非常有用

590
00:10:25,233 --> 00:10:29,500
它同样也很耗电，但能加速周围方块和实体的tick速率

591
00:10:30,033 --> 00:10:32,266
虚空升级能让自动化系统持续运转

592
00:10:32,266 --> 00:10:33,400
尤其是电力系统

593
00:10:34,233 --> 00:10:37,466
超级箱，用于存储大量单一物品

594
00:10:38,400 --> 00:10:41,333
转运器，用于近距离物品和流体运输

595
00:10:41,800 --> 00:10:43,433
这么多好东西可以享受

596
00:10:43,633 --> 00:10:45,833
还有一个要避坑的点

597
00:10:46,600 --> 00:10:48,300
既然你现在不需要那些电路基板了

598
00:10:48,333 --> 00:10:51,533
你很容易会忽略三氯化铁和过硫酸钠

599
00:10:52,066 --> 00:10:53,866
不要忽视这一点

600
00:10:54,000 --> 00:10:55,866
这两样你后面会需要海量

601
00:10:56,033 --> 00:10:58,066
所以你要么好好想想怎么做硫酸

602
00:10:58,066 --> 00:10:59,666
要么想想怎么获得氯

603
00:11:00,233 --> 00:11:01,066
这并不紧急

604
00:11:01,066 --> 00:11:02,866
但是一旦你在HV期间开始需要它

605
00:11:03,000 --> 00:11:05,133
一旦产能跟不上，你会被狠狠卡脖子

606
00:11:05,533 --> 00:11:06,600
你可能也注意到了

607
00:11:06,600 --> 00:11:08,733
这次没有那么多单方块机器任务

608
00:11:08,733 --> 00:11:09,933
习惯吧

609
00:11:10,066 --> 00:11:10,800
但别忘了

610
00:11:10,800 --> 00:11:13,033
所有类型的机器在每个电压都有新版本

611
00:11:13,033 --> 00:11:14,033
他们都更好

612
00:11:14,233 --> 00:11:15,033
除此之外

613
00:11:15,200 --> 00:11:16,266
准备迎接大家伙

614
00:11:16,833 --> 00:11:18,800
新的多方块机器：超净间

615
00:11:18,800 --> 00:11:19,600
月球

616
00:11:19,600 --> 00:11:20,400
钛

617
00:11:20,666 --> 00:11:22,100
应用能源

618
00:11:22,866 --> 00:11:24,333
你真的是初学者了吗？

619
00:11:24,833 --> 00:11:26,233
我想我们会在HV阶段见分晓

620
00:11:26,733 --> 00:11:28,066
第8集见


